items.text:
Rob and I are excited to offer another On Camera Experience for the fall!

6 Classes
October 7th - November 11th 
Tuesdays, 6:30 PM until roughly 9:30 PM
$475 per person (that‚Äôs only $80 per class!)

Class Outline
Class One: Getting to know each other, on camera terms and techniques
Class Two: Commercials
Class Three: Comedy
Class Four: Drama
Class Five: Video Games
Class Six: ‚ÄúOn Set‚Äù - a professional camera op will be filming this class. 

Classes will be a mix of on-camera acting technique and scene study with some acting feedback. All raw footage will be filmed and shared with the students. 

Must join by Tuesday, September 30th.  SPACE IS LIMITED!! To reserve a spot, please contact Sylvia at sylvia@sylviagregorycasting.com

Hope you can be a part of it!

items.text:
Thank you so much for welcoming me to your group!  

I'm a NYC and NJ native, now living in Florida, pursuing acting work to support my film project.  I have significant experience in films.  Supported directors and producers.  I had 5 years as an extra for feature films such as El Cantante, Be Kind/Rewind, and traveled to audition for theatre and short films. Beyond acting, I'm an editor, photographer, and former Spectrum Television production intern with five years of hands-on experience with equipment, and in 2019 created my first show in Western Connecticut, Channel 192, "Spoken Voices."  A passionate advocate against domestic violence. I bring dedication, creativity, and authenticity to every role, and you can find me on FaceBook, "Maribel Brooks" for future auditioning!

Casting Call ‚Äì Mandlig skuespiller/statist s√∏ges

Vi er et hold p√• seks studerende fra VIA Film & Transmedia i Aarhus. I forbindelse med et skoleprojekt samarbejder vi med designer Fie Nielsen og hendes studie, Fj√∂r Studio, om branding af en ny t√∏jkollektion.

Kollektionen udforsker, hvad det vil sige at v√¶re mand i dag, og leger med udtryk, der udfordrer de traditionelle forestillinger om styrke, f√∏lelser og identitet.

Vi s√∏ger en mand i alderen 17‚Äì30 √•r, ca. 180 cm h√∏j, almindelig af bygning og med t√∏jst√∏rrelse small‚Äìmedium.

Praktisk info
 Optagelserne finder sted i Skanderborg
 Mandag den 22/9
 Kl. 09.00‚Äì17.00

Projektet er frivilligt, men vi s√∏rger selvf√∏lgelig for mad, drikke, transport ‚Äì og en sjov oplevelse samt muligheden for at f√• et sp√¶ndende projekt p√• CV‚Äôet.

Hi all, my name is Reuben Carnaby, a student of Film and Television at the University of South Australia. I'm directing our final project in my graduating year, and am looking for anybody interested to be in my film as an extra.

Shooting will be the morning/afternoon of Sunday September 28th.

If interested, please email me at:

reubencarnaby@gmail.com

Or, feel free to shoot me a message!

Thank you,
Reuben

ISO MALE CONTORTIONIST FOR INDEPENDENT FEATURE FILM

A new independent production company, Tu Bruja Productions, is looking for a male contortionist to join the cast of our upcoming project, ‚ÄúThe Return,‚Äù and we would love to source local talent as much as possible. It‚Äôs a psychological thriller, incorporating supernatural elements, and we need a tall male contortionist for some of the spookier bits. The shoot is scheduled for 10/12 for an 18 to 21-day shoot in the Wilmington, NC area, but they would only need to be on set for a day or two. This is a paid opportunity where the rate can be discussed.

If you‚Äôre interested, please email [vvicenty@tubrujaproductions.com](mailto:vvicenty@tubrujaproductions.com) with your resume, reel, and working contact number. Please don‚Äôt DM, as I can‚Äôt read message requests. Thanks in advance!

INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 2nd week in October 2025 (date tbc)

(For actors based in the London area).

 

Summary: A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

 

This project is Episode #0 of ‚ÄòBrave Hunter in Ghost City‚Äô  - introducing a new African story world and some of its main characters. ** **

 

MALE LEAD: to play fearless gangland enforcer.  Black African, 25-45, Lagos accent, 5‚Äô6‚Äù+, athletic physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European,  35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 85kg-100kg,  powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

SUPPORTING MALE: to play dead gangster. White European, 35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 80kg-100kg. Half a day of shooting for ¬£150 for 7 hours.

 

You will need professional experience playing character roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2Filmworks@gmail.com

Tickets are now available for our upcoming Actors and Filmmakers Networking Event, taking place on Sunday, October 26th.

This is a powerful opportunity to connect with a talented cast and crew who can help bring your next project to life.

 

Networking is essential for advancing your career in the industry, and Marble Academy for Drama and Management has proudly facilitated these events for years. With over 90 attendees, our June gathering was a tremendous success, and we are determined to build on that momentum.

 

You will have the opportunity to engage with accomplished actors, visionary directors, prominent producers, and skilled crew members who can offer valuable insights and spark meaningful collaborations.

 

Think about it, if there were an event where you could connect with exceptionally talented cast and crew who could help bring your next project to life, wouldn‚Äôt you want to be there?

 

Take a look at this video from a previous event‚Ä¶..

www.youtube.com/watch?v=EM4jwjRxny4

 

So, join us on Sunday, October 26th, from 2 PM to 6:30 PM at HOME Mcr, located at 2 Tony Wilson Place, Manchester, M15 4FN.

 

Secure your tickets through this link:

www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/actors-and-filmmakers-networking-event-tickets-1509159349239

 

I look forward to seeing you there!

sharedPost.text:
This afternoon we had the pleasure of entertaining a full house for Pettswood WI with our performance of Mr Macabre's Inn. 

The WI is a unique organisation shaped by its members. In 1915, it  set out to give women a voice and to be a force for good in the community. Today, it is the largest women‚Äôs organisation in the UK priding itself on being a trusted place for all women of all generations, to share experiences and learn from each other.

It's 1840, Victorian England‚Ä¶ Deep in the heart of the Kent countryside, not far from the hop farm and the coastline is a secluded little hamlet, with a very old established Inn‚Ä¶
Has Mr. Macabre the Innkeeper being pulling more than pints?
What's the secret ingredient in Mrs. Macabre's popular pies?
Does Tomjon Jones poach more than eggs?

Watch the events unfold and see if you can solve the Murder at Macabre‚Äôs Inn?

Next week we are performing Mr Macabre's Inn on Friday for Sheppey 92.5FM and on Saturday in Boughton Monchelsea, Maidstone.

Casting Call (Non-Union) Paid

Looking for actors to play the role of a client in a simulated therapy session. The video clips will be used in an online training system for counselors and psychologists. The sessions are generally improvised with some prompts or loose scripting.

All ages, all gender expressions/identities, all ethnicities, and persons with disabilities are welcome. We are also very interested in filming with queer couples, interracial couples, or polycules.

Comfortable English fluency is required.

Immediate filming dates are September 23 through 26, but more will occur in the future so please submit if you're interested at all.

Location is downtown Vancouver - Gastown. Pay is 60 cad, duration: 1 hour

Please email phil@skillsetter.com with your headshot and resume. If you've submitted for a past session, you're welcome to submit again.

Thanks! 

Charlie

INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 2nd week in October 2025 (date tbc)

(For actors based in the London area).

 

Summary: A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

 

This project is Episode #0 of ‚ÄòBrave Hunter in Ghost City‚Äô  - introducing a new African story world and some of its main characters. ** **

 

MALE LEAD: to play fearless gangland enforcer.  Black African, 25-45, Lagos accent, 5‚Äô6‚Äù+, athletic physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European,  35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 85kg-100kg,  powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

BACKGROUND MALE: to play dead gangster. White European, 35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 80kg-100kg. Half a day of shooting for ¬£150 for 7 hours.

 

You will need professional experience playing character roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2Filmworks@gmail.com

Hello all, this is another post for a different student film happening on Auraria Campus. I am not involved in this one, I am posting to this group for the producer since he is not on Facebook. So if you are interested in this one please contact the producer. 

Producer- Brennan Jones bjones89@msudenver.edu 

Production Title- The Cost of Greed 

Production Dates- Exact dates are not set but filming will be in October 

Logline- Peter and Henry are sent on a treasure hunt to a house that is believed to be abandoned. Where they then discover it's not a treasure hunt after all and they must face their greed. Either take the treasure or leave empty handed. 

Peter (19-25) Male 

Peter has a moral compass that he deals with during this film. He wants to do the right thing and in the end that pays off for him. 

Henry (19-25) Male 

Henry is a billionaire with no need for more money, however that does not stop him from thinking he needs more. He is corrupt and in the end karma gets to him. 

Audition Dates- September 18th-September 29th

Audition Location- Email-Self Tape

This is a student film for a final project therefore this film is non paid and non union.

Contact Email- bjones89@msudenver.edu 

Must contact the producer to be consider for the role. Once you contact Brennan he will send you the audition material.

items.text:
Hello, we are currently casting for a student film on Auraria Campus! 

Producers- Isabella Coronado & Alanagh Finken 

Production Title- Normal Activity 

Production Dates- We don't have exact dates yet but we do know that we are filming in October. 

Logline- A mocumentary following a college's ghost hunting group as they prepare to explore a haunted local brewery's basement where a spirit has resided for the past thirty years. 

Alex (19-25) Male 

Alex is the leader of the ghost hunting group, he is very enthusiastic. He is clearly the one that is most devoted to this group. 

Chelsea (19-25) Female 

Chelsea is your typical girly girl likes being on camera but does not care about the club she is in. She is pretending to so that the club can get funding for the "haunted (not haunted) hot springs". 

Tommy (19-25) Male 

Tommy is very clearly apart of the club because he has eyes for Chelsea, he could not care less otherwise. 

Vera (19-25) Female 

Vera is Alex's sister and is only there because Alex believes they needed a fourth member and basically bribed Vera to join by saying she could borrow his car whenever she wants. 

Gary (45-55) Male

Logline- A mocumentary following a college's ghost hunting group as they prepare to explore a haunted local brewery's basement where a spirit has resided for the past thirty years. 

Alex (19-25) Male 

Alex is the leader of the ghost hunting group, he is very enthusiastic. He is clearly the one that is most devoted to this group. 

Chelsea (19-25) Female 

Chelsea is your typical girly girl likes being on camera but does not care about the club she is in. She is pretending to so that the club can get funding for the "haunted (not haunted) hot springs". 

Tommy (19-25) Male 

Tommy is very clearly apart of the club because he has eyes for Chelsea, he could not care less otherwise.

F√ºr meinen historisch-romantischen Kurzfilm (1‚Äì3 Minuten) suche ich eine Schauspielpartnerin (25‚Äì30 Jahre) aus Ulm oder Umgebung.

√úber das Projekt:
Es handelt sich um ein Herzensprojekt, nicht bezahlt, daf√ºr mit viel Leidenschaft. Wir drehen eine Szene im Stil klassischer Historienromanzen ‚Äì Spaziergang, Dialoge voller Tiefe, ein erster Kuss und eine leidenschaftliche Kaminszene.

Wichtig:

Keine Scheu oder Scham vor einem Kuss und einer leidenschaftlichen Szene (√§sthetisch, stilvoll, keine Nacktheit).

Du musst keine ausgebildete Schauspielerin sein ‚Äì entscheidend ist deine Spielfreude, Leidenschaft und der Mut, dich auf die Rolle einzulassen.

Wir bieten:

Ein kleines, motiviertes Team

Eine professionelle Umsetzung mit viel Herzblut

Material f√ºr dein Showreel

Eine intensive Erfahrung voller Romantik und Leidenschaft

Es handelt sich um ein Herzensprojekt, nicht bezahlt, daf√ºr mit viel Leidenschaft. Wir drehen eine Szene im Stil klassischer Historienromanzen ‚Äì Spaziergang, Dialoge voller Tiefe, ein erster Kuss und eine leidenschaftliche Kaminszene.

Wichtig:

Keine Scheu oder Scham vor einem Kuss und einer leidenschaftlichen Szene (√§sthetisch, stilvoll, keine Nacktheit).

Du musst keine ausgebildete Schauspielerin sein ‚Äì entscheidend ist deine Spielfreude, Leidenschaft und der Mut, dich auf die Rolle einzulassen.

Wir bieten:

Ein kleines, motiviertes Team

Eine professionelle Umsetzung mit viel Herzblut

Material f√ºr dein Showreel

Eine intensive Erfahrung voller Romantik und Leidenschaft

items.text:
CASTING CALL ‚Äì Short Film
Role: The Woman / The Wild
Production Title: The Judgement of Man
Shooting Dates: November 2025 (Exact dates TBC)
Location: York, North Yorkshire, UK (outdoor, moorland and forest locations)
Compensation: Unpaid ‚Äì expenses covered (travel & food provided)
Festival Goal: 2026 Film Festival Circuit

About the Film:
The Judgement of Man is a dark, medieval-inspired short film exploring themes of judgement, human nature, and decay. The story follows two knight-brothers who, after surviving war, cross a desolate land and encounter a mysterious woman. She is the embodiment of nature itself ‚Äî ancient, wild, and unknowable ‚Äî who exposes the brothers‚Äô true selves and leads them to their downfall.

Role Description ‚Äì The Woman / The Wild:
This character is ethereal, dangerous, and magnetic. She is not merely a person, but a manifestation of the natural order ‚Äî both alluring and terrifying. She appears fragile and otherworldly at first glance, yet holds a deep, unsettling power beneath the surface.
There is no dialogue, so the role requires exceptional physical storytelling and subtle, expressive performance. Think of her presence as a trap: serene and beautiful on the outside, but with an underlying threat.

We are looking for:

‚Ä¢ Female actor, age 20‚Äì35
‚Ä¢ Ability to convey depth and emotion purely through body language, facial expression, and movement
‚Ä¢Comfortable filming outdoors in natural environments (moorland, woodland, night shoots)
‚Ä¢Experience with physical theatre or dance is a bonus

Applicants should submit:
 ‚Ä¢ A recent headshot or clear photograph
 ‚Ä¢ A short showreel or clip (if available)

If you are interested in this project, please apply via the email below! 

edwardthompsonfilm@gmail.com

LOOKING FOR 2 MEN (preferably BASS or BARITONE), 1 WOMAN (preferably ALTO) who can dance and have the ability to harmonize, for our upcoming Holiday Show. 

Ensemble Stage is a professional theater located in Banner Elk, NC which is situated in the Blue Ridge Mtns. in western North Carolina. Our facility consists of over 8000 sq. ft. which includes a 99-seat performance auditorium.

About 90 total hours (rehearsals + performances), no two-show days, no 10-out-of-12's, no more than 3 performances per week (7 total performances). 

contract runs 11/14 thru 12/20.  Fyi- we have no rehearsals Wednesday thru Saturday of Thanksgiving week so you have an opportunity to go be with family if you choose. 

Pay is $260 per week for five weeks (comes to around $14 per hour of actual rehearsal and performance time). Housing is fully provided(includes full kitchen, washer/dryer, wifi, free parking, individual bedroom, no more than two share a bathroom (but usually private) , etc.  Also, no smoking, and no pets (or service animals) are allowed in any housing. 

Round-trip travel reimbursed at $0.25 per mile

Finally,since we are located in the mountains, and since Ensemble Stage does not have a "company car" available for use, having your own vehicle while here is pretty much a necessity. There really is no such thing as walking to the store or to the theatre.

If interested please respond to info@ensemblestage.com, subject- CMAS AUDITIONS. I will then send you details and parameters for you to prepare a video callback audition to be submitted.

# **CASTING CALL!!!!**

**Student Film**

**Non-union**

****PAID****

Hello, I am directing my senior film at the University of Colorado Denver. 

# *Exit Wound*

*One night, one place, one past, two people.*

*Lucy‚Äôs plans for the future unravel when her wounded ex resurfaces, awakening questions and feelings she thought she‚Äôd left behind.*

## *Lucy*

*Female, 22-26, African-American*

*A sharp, ambitious med student is forced to confront old wounds when the man who broke her heart shows up at her door, bleeding and in need.*

## *Christian*

*Male, 22-26, African-American*

*A charming but reckless gangster trying to turn his life around in hopes of a second chance with his lost love.*

**Shoot dates:** Early to** **mid-October 

**Rate:** TBD

****SELF-TAPE Audition** **

Please send a self-tape, resume, and headshot to jenmcfar3@gmail.com. 

*Please submit a self-tape with a couple of different takes.*

**If you have any questions, please contact me at jenmcfar3@gmail.com**

#denveractor #studentfilm #auditions #shortfilmmaking

Hi everyone,
I‚Äôm Callum Foley 24, an actor based in Nottingham. I‚Äôve recently been working on background and student film projects, and I‚Äôm keen to get involved in short films, indie projects, and commercials to build on-screen experience.

I‚Äôm currently training at Nottingham Actors Workshop and working towards joining **Spotlight**, so I‚Äôm looking to create footage that will form my first professional showreel.

I have professional headshots available and would be happy to send them over if you have a role I could be suitable for. I‚Äôm based in Nottingham but happy to travel for projects.

You can reach me at **callumfoley1000@gmail.com**.

Thanks,

items.text:
Hey guys, I'm running a taster session for the screen acting class this Friday for only a fiver! 

In the session, you'll get to practice on a given scene over a couple of takes and I'll also go through the three programs of this autumn: 
* Screen acting drop-in 
* Screen acting Monthly workshop (over 4weeks) to develop presence and get confident on camera. 
* The directing actors Workshop with the last monday of each month with actors in the room! 
* More info at interactors.co.uk @ : info.interactors@gmail.com Make sure you book the ticket for friday via the website if you wish to come! Looking forward to seeing you there!  whttps://www.instagram.com/p/DOeaxfCDLI_/?igsh=MWU0ZHg5aGh5cmI0OQ==

üö®URGENT CASTING CALLüö®

Project Title: SIO: Origins
Production Company: Museboxx M&F
Location: Darbyshire???? TBA (UK-based production)
Deadline: Urgent

Role: Co-Starring Leads ‚Äì Names TBA
We‚Äôre casting for two dynamic male actors to take on a co-starring leading roles in our upcoming production, SIO: Origins, part of the larger SIO universe. The roles are emotionally charged and physically demanding, featuring performance across acting, dance, singing, and occasional stunt choreography. For these roles, We do have places for the characters to appear on the final episode of SIO:Echoes of the SIX - which has been airing throughout this year online. And to be a part of other SIO series', including live performances and other Muaeboxx projects.

Character Traits & Requirements:

‚Ä¢ Sexuality: Gay & Bisexual
‚Ä¢ Age: 26-28
‚Ä¢ Height: 5ft 7 to 6ft
‚Ä¢ Performance Abilities: Singer, Dancer, Acting and Rap
‚Ä¢ Comfortable of doing own Stunts
‚Ä¢ Comfortable with doing Gymnastics
‚Ä¢ No piercings/jewelry

‚Ä¢ Must be available for Live Performances

Previous experience in emotionally intense roles is a bonus

Payment & Contract:
Budget is currently being finalised. Payment details will be discussed at a later stage and confirmed in actor contracts. This will be a credited role with potential for expanded involvement in future series.

To Apply:
Send an email to museboxxmfcasting@gmail.com to send the following: Submit headshot, showreel (if available).
Audition scripts and details will be provided upon application.

If you have any issues with contacting the email above, please don't hesitate to contact our other email below - wintersxperia@gmail.com

More details about the projects will be discussed throughout the Audition process.

items.text:
Hey everyone !! I‚Äôve seen a few people post on here and it‚Äôs given me the courage to do so myself ! 

My name is Cecile, I‚Äôm 23 and I‚Äôm very much starting off in the acting industry (since I‚Äôve just graduated from university with a languages degree). 

I was wondering if anyone had guidance on how to get an agent/work as a new after? 

Also I would love for your opinion for my acting range ?? 
Thanks a bunch !

topComments.text:
Stunning! Best of luck ! 

You could always start with some workshops and training and student short films maybe - to feel more comfortable before you‚Äôve slowly build up your portfolio and are at the stage of approaching agents . 

The photos are amazing, well done !

Your best bet to start with would be to join your local amateur theatre company and/or find a decent acting class for beginners. Establish if you genuinely enjoy acting, and have some talent for it. At the moment it seems more as though you like the IDEA of being an actor. There are a few casting platforms you could join, to apply for acting jobs at the lower end of the ladder, but competition, even for those jobs, is pretty ferocious. It would be be wiser, long-term, to get some experience and training in the much more relaxed world of amateur theatre or classes, before jumping into the professional industry. Get hold of a copy of the Actors and Performers Yearbook, which your local library might have, or could order for you. That will give you an overview into how the UK industry functions, who does what? NEVER pay to join an agency for actors, no matter how much they might flatter you.

items.text: Hello, group! My name is Scott, and I work for an award-winning production company that is developing a new documentary series focused on couples in which one of the members was couch surfing, living out of their van, staying with family, or unhoused when the relationship started. We hope to show the world that everyone deserves love, regardless of their living circumstances. If this applies to you, please see the casting notice below. This is a paid opportunity if selected.

THIS COULD BE YOUR CHANCE to SHARE YOUR STORY! IF IFYOUARE: YOU ARE: DATING IN A LONG-TERM -TERM RELATIONSHIP ENGAGED MARRIED AND EITHER PERSON IN THE RELATIONSHIP WAS LIVING IN SHELTERS, VEHICLE, OR IN-AND-OUT OF FAMILY MEMBERS HOMES WHEN YOU FIRST MET,WE WANT TO HEAR FROM YOU! To apply, please Ao to: https://risis.sganacc .castingcrane.com/ Must be 18+ and legal U.S. resident. See site for full eligibility. We encourage applicants of all backgrounds and experience'

items.text:
Hello, I'm Sunita and something to know about me is that I became full time actor only in 2022 after successful decades as a professor and culture worker. For the last third of my earthly existence I want to help enflesh meaningful inspiring stories with my creative skills primarily as an actor currently, but also as a writer, producer, director. I am also known as Suni M! Yes, with an exclamation point! 

Join me for screening of the short film NANI this Thursday, September 25 at the AMC 16 in Burbank. YES!

INTENSE CRIME DRAMA - SHORT (PAID)

1-day shoot in London (UK) for 2nd week in October 2025 (date tbc)

(For actors based in the London area).

 

Summary: A night of heavy drinking ends in a deadly contest between newfound besties - a fearless Nigerian gangland enforcer and a trigger-happy European gunman.

 

This project is Episode #0 of ‚ÄòBrave Hunter in Ghost City‚Äô  - introducing a new African story world and some of its main characters. ** **

 

MALE LEAD: to play fearless gangland enforcer.  Black African, 25-45, Lagos accent, 5‚Äô6‚Äù+, athletic physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

MALE LEAD: to play trigger-happy gunman. White European,  35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 85kg-100kg,  powerful physique with good fitness and conditioning. Stage combat training. Flat rate of ¬£300 for 15 hours.

 

SUPPORTING MALE: to play dead gangster. White European, 35-45, 5‚Äô 6‚Äù+, 80kg-100kg. Half a day of shooting for ¬£150 for 7 hours.

 

You will need professional experience playing character roles on Stage, Film or TV. Please send in a cover letter, your CV with headshot and your showreel to Davina Brown at k2Filmworks@gmail.com

**Paid Studio Gig ‚Äì Surrey, BC (1‚Äì2 days, max 7 hrs/day)**

Hey Vancouver actors! We‚Äôre producing a batch of short videos for our brand (YouTube, Reels, TikTok, Facebook) and are looking for a confident on-camera presenter to record with us at our Surrey studio.

**What it is:**
* 1‚Äì2 studio days, max **7 hours per day**
* Scripted teleprompter reads + a few simple pickups/B-roll
* We provide the studio, teleprompter, and all gear
* **Contract provided** and **payment in full on wrap**

**You:** Comfortable on camera, friendly, clear delivery, can self-report to Surrey.

**Dates/Rate:** negotiable and flexable 

If you‚Äôre interested, please fill out this form, https://form.jotform.com/252610493666057 

with:
* Headshot + reel/links
* Your availability in **[date range]**
* A quick note confirming you can get to Surrey

Thanks! Excited to meet some local talent.

items.text:
**CASTING CALL "Migraine" - BACKGROUND**

*What if you uncovered something dark buried in a past life?*

Migraine is a psychological-spiritual thriller short film, and we are currently casting background for a **1950s jazz club scene.**

**Details:**
* Age: **19+**
* Gender: **Any **
* Ethnicity:** Any** 
* Location: **Greater Vancouver Area** 
* Rate:** Volunteer. We are a low-budget indie film hyper-focused on quality.** 
* Date: **Sept. 25 or 28**

*please let us know if you available for one or both dates

**CASTING CALL "Migraine" - BACKGROUND**

*What if you uncovered something dark buried in a past life?*

Migraine is a psychological-spiritual thriller short film, and we are currently casting background for a **1950s jazz club scene.**

**Details:**
* Age: **19+**
* Gender: **Any **
* Ethnicity:** Any** 
* Location: **Greater Vancouver Area** 
* Rate:** Volunteer. We are a low-budget indie film hyper-focused on quality.** 
* Date: **Sept. 25 or 28**

*please let us know if you available for one or both dates

To submit please send us your name and contact info at **migraine.shortfilm@gmail.com**

We look forward to working with you!

üé≠ **CASTING CALL ‚Äì New Australian Play in London** üé≠

We are casting **four roles** for an exciting new Australian play, *The Beat of the Bronzewing*, which will have a **showcase reading at the Hen & Chickens Theatre, Islington, on November 12th**.

üå™Ô∏è **About the Play:**
When Peggy shows up at Lorraine‚Äôs shack in dead-end tropical Australia, she brings an irresistible offer: a one-way ticket out of there. But with a cyclone looming and old wounds resurfacing, can Lorraine be convinced she has nothing to lose?

‚ú® Longlisted for the **Theatre 503 International Playwriting Award 2025**, *The Beat of the Bronzewing* explores the lives of three women in remote Australia, grappling with toxic femininity, domestic abuse, and rural isolation. Set against an evocative tropical landscape, the play is a gripping story of friendship, fear, and survival.

üë©‚Äçüé§ **The Team**
‚úçÔ∏è Writer & Producer: Charlotte Churcher
üé¨ Director: Chloe Cattin
ü§ù In partnership with the Australian Women‚Äôs Club London

üìÖ **Key Dates**
* **Auditions:** October 8th (12‚Äì5pm) at the Old Red Lion Theatre, Angel, Islington (alternative arrangements available if needed)
* **Rehearsals:** Sunday 9th November (10am‚Äì6pm) & Wednesday 12th November (from 2:30pm)
* **Showcase:** Tuesday 12th November at Hen & Chickens Theatre

üé≠ **CASTING CALL ‚Äì New Australian Play in London** üé≠

We are casting **four roles** for an exciting new Australian play, *The Beat of the Bronzewing*, which will have a **showcase reading at the Hen & Chickens Theatre, Islington, on November 12th**.

üå™Ô∏è **About the Play:**
When Peggy shows up at Lorraine‚Äôs shack in dead-end tropical Australia, she brings an irresistible offer: a one-way ticket out of there. But with a cyclone looming and old wounds resurfacing, can Lorraine be convinced she has nothing to lose?

‚ú® Longlisted for the **Theatre 503 International Playwriting Award 2025**, *The Beat of the Bronzewing* explores the lives of three women in remote Australia, grappling with toxic femininity, domestic abuse, and rural isolation. Set against an evocative tropical landscape, the play is a gripping story of friendship, fear, and survival.

üë©‚Äçüé§ **The Team**
‚úçÔ∏è Writer & Producer: Charlotte Churcher
üé¨ Director: Chloe Cattin
ü§ù In partnership with the Australian Women‚Äôs Club London

üìÖ **Key Dates**
* **Auditions:** October 8th (12‚Äì5pm) at the Old Red Lion Theatre, Angel, Islington (alternative arrangements available if needed)
* **Rehearsals:** Sunday 9th November (10am‚Äì6pm) & Wednesday 12th November (from 2:30pm)
* **Showcase:** Tuesday 12th November at Hen & Chickens Theatre
